Epidemic Spreading in Temporal NetworksÂ¶

Run notebook in Google Colab
Download notebook
import pathpy as pp

t = pp.TemporalNetwork()
t.add_edge('a', 'b', timestamp=1)
t.add_edge('b', 'c', timestamp=2)
t.add_edge('c', 'd', timestamp=3)
t.plot()

sir = pp.processes.EpidemicSIR(t, recovery_time=1, infection_prob=1)
sir.plot(sir.run_experiment(steps=10, runs=['a']))

t = pp.io.graphtool.read_netzschleuder_network('sp_hospital')
print(t)
t.plot()

Each line has the form ât i j Si Sjâ, where i and j are the anonymous IDs of the persons in contact, Si and Sj are their statuses (NUR=paramedical staff, i.e. nurses and nursesâ aides; PAT=Patient; MED=Medical doctor; ADM=administrative staff), and the interval during which this contact was active is [ t â 20s, t ]. If multiple contacts are active in a given interval, you will see multiple lines starting with the same value of t. Time is measured in seconds.
